This project builds on the following open-source projects. Please consult
their repositories and licenses for further attribution details.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Kokoro-82M — compact TTS model with the inference package we fine-tune.
  Source:  https://github.com/hexgrad/kokoro
  Model:   https://huggingface.co/hexgrad/Kokoro-82M
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Author:  hexgrad
  Usage:   We fine-tune the published Kokoro-82M checkpoint on Marathi data.
           The 178-token Kokoro vocabulary is preserved; slot 144 (a PUA
           placeholder in the upstream table) is repurposed for ɭ (U+026D,
           Marathi retroflex lateral). All other slots are unchanged.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

kokoro-deutsch — the German Kokoro fine-tuning recipe this project forks.
  Source:  https://github.com/semidark/kokoro-deutsch
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Author:  semidark
  Usage:   We use the `kokoro` (semidark/kokoro) and `StyleTTS2`
           (semidark/StyleTTS2) submodules from that project as-is, plus
           a subset of its `scripts/` (dataset prep, voicepack extraction,
           inference testing). Our training flow (Stage 1 → Stage 2 → voicepack
           extraction) follows semidark's recipe directly. Credit for the
           Kokoro-specific training patches (parametrizations migration,
           checkpoint save order, TMA, PLBERT length filter, etc.) belongs
           to semidark and is documented in semidark's repo.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

StyleTTS2 — the TTS training framework Kokoro builds on.
  Source:  https://github.com/yl4579/StyleTTS2
  Fork:    https://github.com/semidark/StyleTTS2 (used via the kokoro-deutsch submodule)
  License: MIT License
  Author:  Yinghao Aaron Li (yl4579)
  Usage:   StyleTTS2 is the training framework (Stage 1 acoustic + alignment,
           Stage 2 prosody + adversarial). We use semidark's fork for
           Kokoro-82M compatibility patches.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

misaki — multilingual G2P used by Kokoro.
  Source:  https://github.com/hexgrad/misaki
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Author:  hexgrad
  Usage:   We use `misaki.espeak.EspeakG2P(language="mr")` for Marathi
           phonemization. Upstream Kokoro pipeline does not ship a Marathi
           lang_code; we monkey-patch `kokoro.pipeline.LANG_CODES["m"] = "mr"`
           at inference time rather than forking the package.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Training datasets (not redistributed in this repo):

  Rasa (AI4Bharat) — Marathi speech corpus, multi-speaker.
    Source:  https://github.com/AI4Bharat/Rasa
    Dataset: https://huggingface.co/datasets/ai4bharat/Rasa
    License: CC-BY-4.0

  IndicVoices-R (AI4Bharat) — gated multi-speaker Indic speech corpus.
    Source:  https://github.com/AI4Bharat/IndicVoices-R
    Dataset: https://huggingface.co/datasets/ai4bharat/indicvoices_r
    License: CC-BY-4.0 (gated access on HuggingFace)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The following directories contain original work by this project's
contributors:

  scripts/     — Marathi dataset preparation, voicepack extraction helpers,
                 inference testing, diagnostics, handoff automation
  configs/     — Marathi fine-tuning configuration (config_marathi_ft.yml,
                 config_mr.json Kokoro inference config with ɭ@144 patch,
                 voice_speeds.json per-voice speed tuning)
  training/    — Marathi-patched symbol table (kokoro_symbols.py with ɭ@144),
                 Marathi TensorBoard inference helpers (kokoro_tb_utils_mr.py),
                 Marathi OOD text set (OOD_texts.txt)
  docs/        — Training guide, troubleshooting, architecture notes for
                 the Marathi adaptation
